	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The trick is to use Quick Grips.
<br />
<br />Line them up on the front cover on both sides, not top and bottom but sides. Slowly gripping it, the cart front will begin to bend upwards, its at that point you can safely use a very, very flat screwdriver or a knife blade so gently ease open the latches. I got this info from the man himself.
<br />
<br />Don't stick anything in the sides or you will end up scratching it all to hell or breaking a latch; an exception is the poorly made multicarts and pirate carts, they usually have easily to open cases.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


