	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Honestly, I doubt these cartridge cases (also pirate Genesis) were designed to be opened. I think they were intended for one-time assembly, and if you lucky, you may take them apart a few times. I broke so much cases I can't even count, no matter how much experience with this I had.
<br />
<br />Genesis ones were easy to repair, at least - there were false plastic screws on the back, so you could cut them and put real screws (heat them to screw into the other side).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
